What is IFSC Code?
IFSC stands for Indian Financial System Code. IFSC code is a 11 character code to identifying the bank and
branch which an account is held. The IFSC code is usually use in RTGS, NEFT and IMPS finance transfer
systems.
Howto Find IFSC Code?
We Provide you very easist way to find the IFSC code for banks in india_ To get the ifsc code first you need to
select the bank, click here to get the list of banks. Just click on bank and get all the information of all branches
like ifsc code, micr code, contact information, addres etc. IFSC Codes
What is IFSC NE-FT transfer?
NEFT stands for National Electronic Funds Transfer, It is a nation-wide system which facilitates individuals,
corporates, firms to electronically transfer amount from any bank branch to any individual, corporate or firm have
an bank account with any other bank branch in the country. It is also known as e-cheques as the amounts are
not transferred in real-time and the amounts are settled in batches.
What is MICR code?
MICR stands for Magnetic Ink Character Recognition MICR is a character recognition technology which primarily
used by the banking industry to facilitate the processing of cheques_ The Micr Codes are generally printed on the
bottom strip of cheque leaf These printed in special typefaces with a magnetic ink or toner, which generally
containing iron oxide Thse code can be easily read by humans This MICR code is used By Reserve bank Of
India (RBI) in clearing process to identify the branch and bank. MICR Codes
